cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.PF, cs.DS 

This paper deals with the design and analysis of a mechanism for forming coalitions of peers in a data swarming system. It involves analyzing the choking and data replication strategies for coalitions, which are relevant to networked systems (cs.NI) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also proposes a cooperation-aware better response strategy, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY) and optimization (cs.PF). Finally, the paper uses extensive simulations to demonstrate improvements in the performance of a swarming system, which is related to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
